    "notes": [
      "Engine mount points lie in the Y-Z plane at x=0 m, 98 mm from the nozzle-exit origin on a 120-degree triangular pattern.",
      "Engine frame axes are built incrementally: (1) thrust reference +X, (2) primary roll axis mount-to-origin, (3) secondary yaw axis perpendicular.",
      "Kinematics: roll (+/-90 deg) is about the fixed primary axis toward origin; yaw (0-135 deg) is about the secondary axis carried through roll (yaw coupled to roll).",
      "Phase 2 intake: vehicle.body_mass_kg is the fixed structure without motors; motor_loaded_mass_kg is per-engine wet propellant mass.",
      "preliminary_total_with_loaded_motors sums body plus three loaded motors for SIH mass-budget review.",
      "Replace masses, COMs, inertia tensors, engine positions, splay axes, trims, backlash, and load-cell calibration with measured bench data before flight.",
      "Large-angle splay is the throttle mechanism; actuator limits, slew rates, and backlash must be measured before hover tests.",
      "CAD visual meshes live under deprecated/sim/gazebo/assets/cad/lander/; STEP sources are not yet checked in for the lander."
